Title: On the SL(2,R) symmetry in Yang-Mills Theories in the Landau,

Curci-Ferrari and Maximal Abelian GaugeAuthors: D. Dudal, V.E.R. Lemes, M. Picariello, M.S. Sarandy, S.P. Sorella, H.

VerscheldeComments: 1+15 pages, LaTeX2e, one reference added

Journal-ref: JHEP 0212 (2002) 008

The existence of a SL(2,R) symmetry is discussed in SU(N) Yang-Mills in themaximal Abelian Gauge. This symmetry, also present in the Landau andCurci-Ferrari gauge, ensures the absence of tachyons in the maximal Abeliangauge. In all these gauges, SL(2,R) turns out to be dynamically broken by ghostcondensates.